Your nesting of the rules is off. Since you never close the `{` that is after `MoviesnShows`, your rules for `Booster` are at path `Apps/MoviesnShows/Booster`.

To fix this, close the `MoviesnShows` node with `}`:
```
&quot;Apps&quot;: {
  &quot;MoviesnShows&quot;: {
    &quot;.indexOn&quot;:[&quot;downloads&quot;,&quot;upvote&quot;,&quot;H20&quot;]
  },
  &quot;Booster&quot;:{
    &quot;.indexOn&quot;:[&quot;downloads&quot;,&quot;upvote&quot;,&quot;H20&quot;]
  }
}
```

---

If you have more nodes like `MoviesnShows` and `Booster`, you can consider using a [wildcard capture rule](https://firebase.google.com/docs/database/security/core-syntax#wildcard_capture_variables) to define the indexes for all of them in one go:

```
&quot;Apps&quot;: {
  &quot;$topic&quot;: {
    &quot;.indexOn&quot;:[&quot;downloads&quot;,&quot;upvote&quot;,&quot;H20&quot;]
  }
}
```

